************************************  Map  *****************************************************
: map is part of STL, which can store the key value pair 
key is nothing but its uniqe indeitifer.
and value means data

example :
Roll Number -> Student Name
Employee ID -> Employee Name
Vehicle Number -> Owner Name
Word -> Meaning

syntax of map:

std::map<key_value_type, data_value_type> map_variable_name;
std::map<int,std::string> emp;


* Map stored data in shorted order by key.

🎯 Example 1: Employee Database
#include<iostream>
#include<map>

int main()
{
    std::map<int,std::string> emp;

    emp[1001] = "Ankur";
    emp[1002] = "Ram";
    emp[1003] = "Shyam";

    std::cout << emp[1002];

    return 0;
}

Output:

Ram


it->first point to key
it->second point to data





